
                                            Three vehicles crashed on the N1 on Monday afternoon.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Three people have been killed following a collision near Worcester. Three vehicles crashed on the N1 on Monday afternoon. It’s understood one person was still trapped in the wreckage. Provincial traffic chief Kenny Africa said: “We are pleading to the motorists to please when you are on the M1 between Worcester and Paarl, please be patient. We will try and reopen the N1 as soon as possible. Currently, we’ve got a stop-go situation at the accident scene.”